# Secrets and credentials

## Do not commit
- Passwords, API keys, Supabase **service_role** key, OAuth secrets, GitHub/GitLab PATs in URLs or files
- `.env.local` (keep gitignored); document only **variable names** in AGENTS / README

## Seed script (`scripts/seed-test-users.mjs`)
- Passwords: `TEST_PASSWORD` env **or** interactive prompt only — no literals in repo
- Example placeholders in comments are OK; real secrets are never checked in

## Git remote
- Use SSH or credential helper — **never** embed a PAT in `git remote` URL (rotate if leaked)

## Server-only keys
- `SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY` → only `src/lib/supabase-admin.js` and server API routes — never `NEXT_PUBLIC_*`
- **`feature_flags.payload`** is public (`GET /api/feature-flags`) — never API keys or PII.
